                                <h5 class="card-title">2. Virechana (Purgation Therapy)</h5>
                                <p class="card-text">Controlled purgation to eliminate excess Pitta dosha and toxins from the liver, gallbladder, and small intestine.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
                        <div class="card h-100">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h5 class="card-title">3. Basti (Enema Therapy)</h5>
                                <p class="card-text">Medicated enemas to balance Vata dosha and cleanse the colon, considered the most important of all Panchakarma procedures.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
                        <div class="card h-100">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h5 class="card-title">4. Nasya (Nasal Administration)</h5>
                                <p class="card-text">Administration of medicated substances through the nose to cleanse and treat disorders related to the head and neck.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="col-12 mb-4">
